Bet you
            didn’t know that. . .


            Aggregates are the only
            mineral commodity produced in every state in the union.
            Every year more than two billion tons of this material
            are used in the United States. 


            In other words, approximately eight
            tons of aggregates are used for every American each year.
            That’s 16,000 pounds or a total of 107 average sized
            people standing on the scale at one time!
            

Imagine life without . . .

 
 
 

            highways · paint · plastics · medicines ·
            glass · driveways · concrete sidewalks ·
            bridges · wallboard · vinyl · brick and stone
            buildings and homes · concrete blocks · roofing
            tiles · asphalt shingles · minerals for
            agriculture

.. all these things are
            made possible with crushed stone products ..


 
 








AND . . .



            More than a million
            employees and their families 
            rely on the country’s
            construction materials industries for their livelihoods.
            Many live and work in your community. Thousands of
            other folks rely on this resource and industry to make
            possible other things like schools, hospitals, and
            airports. Rogers Group employs 1,700 people and does
            business in 5 states and numerous communities.



            Rogers Group and our industry maintain a strong
            commitment to safety and health at our workplaces. We
            comply with stringent federal, state, and local
            regulations. Our safety and health training programs have
            helped us develop a knowledgeable workforce. With a
            history of outstanding safety records, 34 of our
            locations had zero accidents this past year
            alone.


 
Did
            you realize . . .




            Many of our people
            are quite often active leaders in the community, involved
            with local schools, civic groups, community projects, and
            organizations like Little League.

            . . . Rogers Group
            emphasizes aesthetics and environmental considerations.
            We have won many industry and community awards for our
            site beautification efforts in providing dust and noise
            control, landscaping, truck routing, and attractive
            entrance designs. 
 

 

            . . . and that crushed stone is becoming a critical tool
            used to protect our environment. Erosion control programs
            require stone. Water and sewer facilities use stone and
            sand for filtration systems. Utility power plants use
            crushed stone to reduce sulfur dioxide that produces acid
            rain. Rogers Group has been nationally recognized for our
            environmental efforts. 
 
 
            . . . and outstanding community developments occur as a
            result of quarry reclamation. Local and state parks,
            wildlife areas, and golf courses are just some of the
            many beautiful places you can visit because of a quarry. 
 




. . . Finally, every small town,every big city, and every road and building
in them are built with stone!




















